title: Google\Cloud\Eventarc\V1\ChannelConnection
name: ChannelConnection
description:
A representation of the ChannelConnection resource.

A ChannelConnection is a resource which event providers create during the activation process to establish a connection between the provider and the subscriber channel.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.eventarc.v1.ChannelConnection

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.uid
params.description: Output only. Server assigned ID of the resource. The server guarantees uniqueness and immutability until deleted.

params.name: data.channel
params.description: Required. The name of the connected subscriber Channel. This is a weak reference to avoid cross project and cross accounts references. This must be in projects/{project}/location/{location}/channels/{channel_id} format.

params.name: data.activation_token
params.description: Input only. Activation token for the channel. The token will be used during the creation of ChannelConnection to bind the channel with the provider project. This field will not be stored in the provider resource.
